1. Execute smoke testing for VSCT-QA environment. 
2. Clear cache, clear local storage in browser
3. Upload variables from config.js
4. Sign in as a FRONT_ADMIN via standart form
5. Execute regression testing. Use file Frontend.TestSuit.xml
6. For Admin site/Back office scenariors open a new tab or switches between tabs and go to new BACK URL
7. Open console and keep it open (Webkit browser > Develop > Shown Web Inspector > Console > Errors)
8. After any action fetch errors in console and print if any critical exist
9. Create a report after each section (ID, Title, Result, Detailed error)
10. If the bugs were found create a bug report with Test case ID


